Kim Hansen is the Executive Producer and CEO at Voxiter Technologies. A veteran web/mobile/video game designer and thought leader, she cut her teeth as QA Team Lead for Mass Effect 1 and 2 at BioWare where she worked closely with the design team to create one of the best-loved video game franchises in history, selling over 7 million copies worldwide.

A distinctly technical, creative mind, Kim is an expert at doing much with little — in 2013, she lead the design team on the highly-rated Everlove: Rose, a project with Silicon Sisters. She went on to lead a small team of creatives and developers to create a never-before-seen user experience for the successfully greenlit EON Altar, a table-top roleplaying adventure to be enjoyed by up to 4 players using mobile devices as controllers.

Moving on from games, Kim and socilogica's CTO Mike Cora worked together to create socilogica.’s Rewardlogic gamified customer engagement platform. Rewardlogic features a fully scriptable RPG engine and iBeacon augmented reality. The platform is currently installed at dozens of Harley-Davidson® dealerships around the world.

Early in 2015, Kim left socilogica. to begin ideation on Voxiter and to join BlackPurl Technologies as a Senior Interaction Consultant. There, Kim worked with a small team of area experts and outsourcing partners MetaCube Software to create BlackPurl MVP, a gamified Point of Sale and Order Processing solution. The Minimum Viable Product the team created was instrumental in raising a $3M seed round.
